Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of text data from various sources like social media and forums. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing sentiment trends on social media platforms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely category as the paper discusses the use of a prediction model to generate real-time graphs on sentiment trends. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the design and implementation of a re-usable document regression pipeline as a framework.
